# Fixture: fm2-minus-no-shared-variable
# Finding: Failure Mode 2 — MINUS with disjoint variable sets
# Spec: SPARQL 1.1 §12.6 (MINUS formal definition)
# Mailing list: public-sparql-dev "MINUS semantics" (2014)
#
# Hypothesis: MINUS removes only solutions from the left that "share at least
# one variable" with a matching solution on the right. Here the right-hand
# pattern introduces fresh variables ?x and ?y that do not appear on the left
# (?s and ?o). Per §12.6, MINUS must have NO effect — all left solutions
# survive regardless of whether the right pattern matches any data.
#
# Divergence: An implementation that treats MINUS like FILTER NOT EXISTS
# (i.e., removes any left solution when the right pattern has *any* solution
# in the dataset) incorrectly eliminates solutions when the datasets for
# right-side variables are non-empty.
# Expected grammar-level behaviour: parses successfully.

SELECT * WHERE {
  ?s <http://example/p> ?o .
  MINUS {
    ?x <http://example/q> ?y .
  }
}
